# Up Final Integration Rule (Firebase / Google)

## Reuse-First Policy
- Prefer reusing proven integration logic from reference projects when compatible.
- Reuse existing auth/data contract where it reduces risk and effort.
- Preserve behavior first; optimize structure second.
- Keep local-first data flows as default for core features.

## Required Refactor Boundaries
- Move integration code into `src/services/`.
- Components must not call Firebase/Auth SDK directly.
- Wrap side effects in service methods with explicit input/output contracts.
- Entitlement checks must be evaluated before leaderboard service calls.

## Environment and Secrets
- No hardcoded keys or project config in source files.
- Use `.env` + `import.meta.env` for runtime configuration.
- Keep environment names consistent and documented.

## Data Safety
- Validate write payloads before persistence.
- Handle empty/null/error states explicitly in service responses.
- Do not silently swallow integration errors.

## Leaderboard Cost Controls
- Non-Pro users must not trigger Firestore leaderboard read/write calls.
- Leaderboard writes must be summary-only and best-score-only updates.
- Enforce upload throttling per user (for example, max 3 uploads/hour).
- Enforce leaderboard caching (TTL + background refresh) to reduce repeated reads.
